1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4279 By: Miller
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to Oklahoma Department of Veterans
Affairs; amending 72 O.S. 2021, Section 222, as
8 amended by Section 2, Chapter 42, O.S.L. 2024 (72
O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 222); renaming and
9 reclassifying a fund; amending authorized revenues
into fund; prohibiting state appropriations into
10 fund; exempting fund from certain actions; requiring
the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs to keep
11 certain records; requiring certain audits; requiring
certain reports; providing an effective date; and
12 declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 72 O.S. 2021, Section 222, as
17 amended by Section 2, Chapter 42, O.S.L. 2024 (72 O.S. Supp. 2025,
18 Section 222), is amended to read as follows:
19 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
20 fund an agency special account for the Oklahoma Department of
21 Veterans Affairs to be known as the "Oklahoma Department of Veterans
22 Affairs Revolving Nonappropriated Veteran Care Enterprise Fund".
23 The revolving fund agency special account shall consist of all funds
24 and monies received by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs,
Req. No. 15897 Page 1

1 its constituent institutions, and/or or the Oklahoma Veterans
2 Commission, from any gifts, contributions, bequests, individual
3 reimbursements fees for service except as otherwise provided by law,
4 and other sources of revenue, for the care or support of war
5 veterans discharged other than under dishonorable conditions, who
6 have been admitted and cared for at the Oklahoma Department of
7 Veterans Affairs Centers Homes at Ardmore, Claremore, Clinton,
8 Lawton/Ft. Sill, Norman, Sulphur or Sallisaw. Provided, no grants-
9 in-aid, reimbursements, or other revenue from the United States
10 government or any instrumentality of the United States government,
11 or state appropriations shall be deposited in the fund. Provided
12 further, nothing contained herein prohibits the establishment and
13 utilization of special agency accounts by the Oklahoma Department of
14 Veterans Affairs and its constituent institutions, as may be
15 approved by the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
16 Services, for receipt and disbursement of the personal funds of
17 Veteran Center Home patients and members residents and/or for
18 receipt and disbursement of charitable contributions and donations
19 for use by and for patients and members residents.
20 B. The revolving fund agency special account herein created
21 shall be used by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs to pay
22 for the care of war veterans discharged other than under
23 dishonorable conditions, in Veterans Centers Homes, to pay the
24 general operating expenses of the Veterans Centers Homes, including
Req. No. 15897 Page 2

1 the payment of salaries and wages of officials and employees, to pay
2 for the employee safety programs and incentive awards provided for
3 in Section 63.10a of this title, and to remodel, repair, construct,
4 build additions, modernize, or add improvements of domiciliary or
5 hospital buildings necessary for the care of veterans, including
6 tuberculosis, mentally ill or neuropsychiatric patients, but not
7 excluding others; and architectural plans, specifications, or other
8 costs pertinent thereto.
9 C. The Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs may transfer
10 monies from the revolving fund created in this section to the W.V.C.
11 Revolving Fund in the State Treasury.
12 D. All expenditures from the revolving fund shall be made upon
13 warrants issued by the State Treasurer based upon claims approved by
14 the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs, as provided by law, and
15 filed with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
16 Services for approval and payment agency special account are exempt
17 from the requirement of deposit in the State Treasury and from
18 disbursement through the Office of Management and Enterprise
19 Services.
20 D. The Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs shall:
21 1. Maintain accounting records for exempt funds on a basis
22 consistent with applicable federal requirements;
23 2. Submit quarterly informational reports to the Governor,
24 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro
Req. No. 15897 Page 3

1 Temp ore of the Oklahoma State Senate, and the Director of Office of
2 Management and Enterprise Services identifying sources, amounts,
3 purposes, and expenditures of such funds; and
4 3. Remain subject to examination by the State Auditor and
5 Inspector and to all federal audit and compliance requirements.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
7 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
8 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
